formatProductionTime

public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> formatProductionTime()
Returns a hashmap representing the production time of the building. Key "m" for minutes ; Key "s" for seconds. e.g. : BuildingSnapshot b = new BuildingSnapshot(); b.productionTime = 3605; String s = b.formatProductionTime("m") + " minutes" + b.formatProductionTime("s") + " seconds". This would give 60 minutes 5 seconds. Note: this is the same method as in the Building class.

Returns:
HashMap
